# 16.20 Final Summary

The Study Abroad Finder demonstrates a complete AI application built around modern AI engineering principles.

The project integrates:

- Google Gemini 2.5 Flash for reasoning
- Google ADK for orchestration
- Multiple MCP servers for specialized execution
- Docker for runtime standardization
- Render for cloud deployment

Throughout the project, every architectural layer was designed to remain modular and replaceable.

The resulting system serves not only as a functional application but also as a reusable reference architecture for future AI systems built on tool orchestration, standardized protocols, and cloud-native deployment.

This document captures the complete lifecycle of the project—from architecture and implementation to debugging, deployment, validation, production readiness, and future evolution—providing a comprehensive reference for developers, engineers, and future maintainers.